22#define PACK(s) ((size_t)(s)<<(sizeof(size_t)*8-16))
23#define REDUCE1BIT(V) do { \
24 if (sizeof(size_t)==8) { \
25 u64 T = U64(0xe100000000000000) & (0-(V.lo&1)); \
26 V.lo = (V.hi<<63)|(V.lo>>1); \
27 V.hi = (V.hi>>1 )^T; \
28 } \
29 else { \
30 u32 T = 0xe1000000U & (0-(u32)(V.lo&1)); \
31 V.lo = (V.hi<<63)|(V.lo>>1); \
32 V.hi = (V.hi>>1 )^((u64)T<<32); \
33 } \
34} while(0)

36/*-
37 * Even though permitted values for TABLE_BITS are 8, 4 and 1, it should
38 * never be set to 8. 8 is effectively reserved for testing purposes.
39 * TABLE_BITS>1 are lookup-table-driven implementations referred to as
40 * "Shoup's" in GCM specification. In other words OpenSSL does not cover
41 * whole spectrum of possible table driven implementations. Why? In
42 * non-"Shoup's" case memory access pattern is segmented in such manner,
43 * that it's trivial to see that cache timing information can reveal
44 * fair portion of intermediate hash value. Given that ciphertext is
45 * always available to attacker, it's possible for him to attempt to
46 * deduce secret parameter H and if successful, tamper with messages
47 * [which is nothing but trivial in CTR mode]. In "Shoup's" case it's
48 * not as trivial, but there is no reason to believe that it's resistant
49 * to cache-timing attack. And the thing about "8-bit" implementation is
50 * that it consumes 16 (sixteen) times more memory, 4KB per individual
51 * key + 1KB shared. Well, on pros side it should be twice as fast as
52 * "4-bit" version. And for gcc-generated x86[_64] code, "8-bit" version
53 * was observed to run ~75% faster, closer to 100% for commercial
54 * compilers... Yet "4-bit" procedure is preferred, because it's
55 * believed to provide better security-performance balance and adequate
56 * all-round performance. "All-round" refers to things like:
57 *
58 * - shorter setup time effectively improves overall timing for
59 * handling short messages;
60 * - larger table allocation can become unbearable because of VM
61 * subsystem penalties (for example on Windows large enough free
62 * results in VM working set trimming, meaning that consequent
63 * malloc would immediately incur working set expansion);
64 * - larger table has larger cache footprint, which can affect
65 * performance of other code paths (not necessarily even from same
66 * thread in Hyper-Threading world);
67 *
68 * Value of 1 is not appropriate for performance reasons.
69 */

72static void gcm_init_8bit(u128 Htable[256], u64 H[2])
73{
74 int i, j;
75 u128 V;
76
77 Htable[0].hi = 0;
78 Htable[0].lo = 0;
79 V.hi = H[0];
80 V.lo = H[1];
81
82 for (Htable[128] = V, i = 64; i > 0; i >>= 1) {
83 REDUCE1BIT(V);
84 Htable[i] = V;
85 }
86
87 for (i = 2; i < 256; i <<= 1) {
88 u128 *Hi = Htable + i, H0 = *Hi;
89 for (j = 1; j < i; ++j) {
90 Hi[j].hi = H0.hi ^ Htable[j].hi;
91 Hi[j].lo = H0.lo ^ Htable[j].lo;
92 }
93 }
94}

216static void gcm_init_4bit(u128 Htable[16], u64 H[2])
217{
218 u128 V;
219# if defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
220 int i;
221# endif
222
223 Htable[0].hi = 0;
224 Htable[0].lo = 0;
225 V.hi = H[0];
226 V.lo = H[1];
227
228# if defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
229 for (Htable[8] = V, i = 4; i > 0; i >>= 1) {
230 REDUCE1BIT(V);
231 Htable[i] = V;
232 }
233
234 for (i = 2; i < 16; i <<= 1) {
235 u128 *Hi = Htable + i;
236 int j;
237 for (V = *Hi, j = 1; j < i; ++j) {
238 Hi[j].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[j].hi;
239 Hi[j].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[j].lo;
240 }
241 }
242# else
243 Htable[8] = V;
244 REDUCE1BIT(V);
245 Htable[4] = V;
246 REDUCE1BIT(V);
247 Htable[2] = V;
248 REDUCE1BIT(V);
249 Htable[1] = V;
250 Htable[3].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[2].hi, Htable[3].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[2].lo;
251 V = Htable[4];
252 Htable[5].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[1].hi, Htable[5].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[1].lo;
253 Htable[6].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[2].hi, Htable[6].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[2].lo;
254 Htable[7].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[3].hi, Htable[7].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[3].lo;
255 V = Htable[8];
256 Htable[9].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[1].hi, Htable[9].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[1].lo;
257 Htable[10].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[2].hi, Htable[10].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[2].lo;
258 Htable[11].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[3].hi, Htable[11].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[3].lo;
259 Htable[12].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[4].hi, Htable[12].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[4].lo;
260 Htable[13].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[5].hi, Htable[13].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[5].lo;
261 Htable[14].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[6].hi, Htable[14].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[6].lo;
262 Htable[15].hi = V.hi ^ Htable[7].hi, Htable[15].lo = V.lo ^ Htable[7].lo;
263# endif
264# if defined(GHASH_ASM) && (defined(__arm__) || defined(__arm))
265 /*
266 * ARM assembler expects specific dword order in Htable.
267 */
268 {
269 int j;
270 const union {
271 long one;
272 char little;
273 } is_endian = { 1 };
274
275 if (is_endian.little)
276 for (j = 0; j < 16; ++j) {
277 V = Htable[j];
278 Htable[j].hi = V.lo;
279 Htable[j].lo = V.hi;
280 } else
281 for (j = 0; j < 16; ++j) {
282 V = Htable[j];
283 Htable[j].hi = V.lo << 32 | V.lo >> 32;
284 Htable[j].lo = V.hi << 32 | V.hi >> 32;
285 }
286 }
287# endif
288}

298static void gcm_gmult_4bit(u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16])
299{
300 u128 Z;
301 int cnt = 15;
302 size_t rem, nlo, nhi;
303 const union {
304 long one;
305 char little;
306 } is_endian = { 1 };
307
308 nlo = ((const u8 *)Xi)[15];
309 nhi = nlo >> 4;
310 nlo &= 0xf;
311
312 Z.hi = Htable[nlo].hi;
313 Z.lo = Htable[nlo].lo;
314
315 while (1) {
316 rem = (size_t)Z.lo & 0xf;
317 Z.lo = (Z.hi << 60) | (Z.lo >> 4);
318 Z.hi = (Z.hi >> 4);
319 if (sizeof(size_t) == 8)
320 Z.hi ^= rem_4bit[rem];
321 else
322 Z.hi ^= (u64)rem_4bit[rem] << 32;
323
324 Z.hi ^= Htable[nhi].hi;
325 Z.lo ^= Htable[nhi].lo;
326
327 if (--cnt < 0)
328 break;
329
330 nlo = ((const u8 *)Xi)[cnt];
331 nhi = nlo >> 4;
332 nlo &= 0xf;
333
334 rem = (size_t)Z.lo & 0xf;
335 Z.lo = (Z.hi << 60) | (Z.lo >> 4);
336 Z.hi = (Z.hi >> 4);
337 if (sizeof(size_t) == 8)
338 Z.hi ^= rem_4bit[rem];
339 else
340 Z.hi ^= (u64)rem_4bit[rem] << 32;
341
342 Z.hi ^= Htable[nlo].hi;
343 Z.lo ^= Htable[nlo].lo;
344 }
345
346 if (is_endian.little) {
347# ifdef BSWAP8
348 Xi[0] = BSWAP8(Z.hi);
349 Xi[1] = BSWAP8(Z.lo);
350# else
351 u8 *p = (u8 *)Xi;
352 u32 v;
353 v = (u32)(Z.hi >> 32);
354 PUTU32(p, v);
355 v = (u32)(Z.hi);
356 PUTU32(p + 4, v);
357 v = (u32)(Z.lo >> 32);
358 PUTU32(p + 8, v);
359 v = (u32)(Z.lo);
360 PUTU32(p + 12, v);
361# endif
362 } else {
363 Xi[0] = Z.hi;
364 Xi[1] = Z.lo;
365 }
366}

462 0xCB70, 0xCAB2, 0xC8F4, 0xC936, 0xCC78, 0xCDBA, 0xCFFC, 0xCE3E,
463 0x9180, 0x9042, 0x9204, 0x93C6, 0x9688, 0x974A, 0x950C, 0x94CE,
464 0x9F90, 0x9E52, 0x9C14, 0x9DD6, 0x9898, 0x995A, 0x9B1C, 0x9ADE,
465 0x8DA0, 0x8C62, 0x8E24, 0x8FE6, 0x8AA8, 0x8B6A, 0x892C, 0x88EE,
466 0x83B0, 0x8272, 0x8034, 0x81F6, 0x84B8, 0x857A, 0x873C, 0x86FE,
467 0xA9C0, 0xA802, 0xAA44, 0xAB86, 0xAEC8, 0xAF0A, 0xAD4C, 0xAC8E,
468 0xA7D0, 0xA612, 0xA454, 0xA596, 0xA0D8, 0xA11A, 0xA35C, 0xA29E,
469 0xB5E0, 0xB422, 0xB664, 0xB7A6, 0xB2E8, 0xB32A, 0xB16C, 0xB0AE,
470 0xBBF0, 0xBA32, 0xB874, 0xB9B6, 0xBCF8, 0xBD3A, 0xBF7C, 0xBEBE
471 };
472 /*
473 * This pre-processing phase slows down procedure by approximately
474 * same time as it makes each loop spin faster. In other words
475 * single block performance is approximately same as straightforward
476 * "4-bit" implementation, and then it goes only faster...
477 */
478 for (cnt = 0; cnt < 16; ++cnt) {
479 Z.hi = Htable[cnt].hi;
480 Z.lo = Htable[cnt].lo;
481 Hshr4[cnt].lo = (Z.hi << 60) | (Z.lo >> 4);
482 Hshr4[cnt].hi = (Z.hi >> 4);
483 Hshl4[cnt] = (u8)(Z.lo << 4);
484 }
485
486 do {
487 for (Z.lo = 0, Z.hi = 0, cnt = 15; cnt; --cnt) {
488 nlo = ((const u8 *)Xi)[cnt];
489 nlo ^= inp[cnt];
490 nhi = nlo >> 4;
491 nlo &= 0xf;
492
493 Z.hi ^= Htable[nlo].hi;
494 Z.lo ^= Htable[nlo].lo;
495
496 rem = (size_t)Z.lo & 0xff;
497
498 Z.lo = (Z.hi << 56) | (Z.lo >> 8);
499 Z.hi = (Z.hi >> 8);
500
501 Z.hi ^= Hshr4[nhi].hi;
502 Z.lo ^= Hshr4[nhi].lo;
503 Z.hi ^= (u64)rem_8bit[rem ^ Hshl4[nhi]] << 48;
504 }
505
506 nlo = ((const u8 *)Xi)[0];
507 nlo ^= inp[0];
508 nhi = nlo >> 4;
509 nlo &= 0xf;
510
511 Z.hi ^= Htable[nlo].hi;
512 Z.lo ^= Htable[nlo].lo;
513
514 rem = (size_t)Z.lo & 0xf;
515
516 Z.lo = (Z.hi << 60) | (Z.lo >> 4);
517 Z.hi = (Z.hi >> 4);
518
519 Z.hi ^= Htable[nhi].hi;
520 Z.lo ^= Htable[nhi].lo;
521 Z.hi ^= ((u64)rem_8bit[rem << 4]) << 48;
522# endif
523
524 if (is_endian.little) {
525# ifdef BSWAP8
526 Xi[0] = BSWAP8(Z.hi);
527 Xi[1] = BSWAP8(Z.lo);
528# else
529 u8 *p = (u8 *)Xi;
530 u32 v;
531 v = (u32)(Z.hi >> 32);
532 PUTU32(p, v);
533 v = (u32)(Z.hi);
534 PUTU32(p + 4, v);
535 v = (u32)(Z.lo >> 32);
536 PUTU32(p + 8, v);
537 v = (u32)(Z.lo);
538 PUTU32(p + 12, v);
539# endif
540 } else {
541 Xi[0] = Z.hi;
542 Xi[1] = Z.lo;
543 }
544 } while (inp += 16, len -= 16);
545}
546# endif
547# else
548void gcm_gmult_4bit(u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16]);
549void gcm_ghash_4bit(u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16], const u8 *inp,
550 size_t len);
551# endif
552
553# define GCM_MUL(ctx) gcm_gmult_4bit(ctx->Xi.u,ctx->Htable)
554# if defined(GHASH_ASM) || !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
555# define GHASH(ctx,in,len) gcm_ghash_4bit((ctx)->Xi.u,(ctx)->Htable,in,len)
556/*
557 * GHASH_CHUNK is "stride parameter" missioned to mitigate cache trashing
558 * effect. In other words idea is to hash data while it's still in L1 cache
559 * after encryption pass...
560 */
561# define GHASH_CHUNK (3*1024)
562# endif

566static void gcm_gmult_1bit(u64 Xi[2], const u64 H[2])
567{
568 u128 V, Z = { 0, 0 };
569 long X;
570 int i, j;
571 const long *xi = (const long *)Xi;
572 const union {
573 long one;
574 char little;
575 } is_endian = { 1 };
576
577 V.hi = H[0]; /* H is in host byte order, no byte swapping */
578 V.lo = H[1];
579
580 for (j = 0; j < 16 / sizeof(long); ++j) {
581 if (is_endian.little) {
582 if (sizeof(long) == 8) {
583# ifdef BSWAP8
584 X = (long)(BSWAP8(xi[j]));
585# else
586 const u8 *p = (const u8 *)(xi + j);
587 X = (long)((u64)GETU32(p) << 32 | GETU32(p + 4));
588# endif
589 } else {
590 const u8 *p = (const u8 *)(xi + j);
591 X = (long)GETU32(p);
592 }
593 } else
594 X = xi[j];
595
596 for (i = 0; i < 8 * sizeof(long); ++i, X <<= 1) {
597 u64 M = (u64)(X >> (8 * sizeof(long) - 1));
598 Z.hi ^= V.hi & M;
599 Z.lo ^= V.lo & M;
600
601 REDUCE1BIT(V);
602 }
603 }
604
605 if (is_endian.little) {
606# ifdef BSWAP8
607 Xi[0] = BSWAP8(Z.hi);
608 Xi[1] = BSWAP8(Z.lo);
609# else
610 u8 *p = (u8 *)Xi;
611 u32 v;
612 v = (u32)(Z.hi >> 32);
613 PUTU32(p, v);
614 v = (u32)(Z.hi);
615 PUTU32(p + 4, v);
616 v = (u32)(Z.lo >> 32);
617 PUTU32(p + 8, v);
618 v = (u32)(Z.lo);
619 PUTU32(p + 12, v);
620# endif
621 } else {
622 Xi[0] = Z.hi;
623 Xi[1] = Z.lo;
624 }
625}
626
627# define GCM_MUL(ctx) gcm_gmult_1bit(ctx->Xi.u,ctx->H.u)
628
629#endif

717void CRYPTO_gcm128_init(GCM128_CONTEXT *ctx, void *key, block128_f block)
718{
719 const union {
720 long one;
721 char little;
722 } is_endian = { 1 };
723
724 memset(ctx, 0, sizeof(*ctx));
725 ctx->block = block;
726 ctx->key = key;
727
728 (*block) (ctx->H.c, ctx->H.c, key);
729
730 if (is_endian.little) {
731 /* H is stored in host byte order */
732#ifdef BSWAP8
733 ctx->H.u[0] = BSWAP8(ctx->H.u[0]);
734 ctx->H.u[1] = BSWAP8(ctx->H.u[1]);
735#else
736 u8 *p = ctx->H.c;
737 u64 hi, lo;
738 hi = (u64)GETU32(p) << 32 | GETU32(p + 4);
739 lo = (u64)GETU32(p + 8) << 32 | GETU32(p + 12);
740 ctx->H.u[0] = hi;
741 ctx->H.u[1] = lo;
742#endif
743 }
744#if TABLE_BITS==8
745 gcm_init_8bit(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
746#elif TABLE_BITS==4
747# if defined(GHASH)
748# define CTX__GHASH(f) (ctx->ghash = (f))
749# else
750# define CTX__GHASH(f) (ctx->ghash = NULL)
751# endif
752# if defined(GHASH_ASM_X86_OR_64)
753# if !defined(GHASH_ASM_X86) || defined(OPENSSL_IA32_SSE2)
754 if (OPENSSL_ia32cap_P[1] & (1 << 1)) { /* check PCLMULQDQ bit */
755 if (((OPENSSL_ia32cap_P[1] >> 22) & 0x41) == 0x41) { /* AVX+MOVBE */
756 gcm_init_avx(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
757 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_avx;
758 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_avx);
759 } else {
760 gcm_init_clmul(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
761 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_clmul;
762 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_clmul);
763 }
764 return;
765 }
766# endif
767 gcm_init_4bit(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
768# if defined(GHASH_ASM_X86) /* x86 only */
769# if defined(OPENSSL_IA32_SSE2)
770 if (OPENSSL_ia32cap_P[0] & (1 << 25)) { /* check SSE bit */
771# else
772 if (OPENSSL_ia32cap_P[0] & (1 << 23)) { /* check MMX bit */
773# endif
774 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_4bit_mmx;
775 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_4bit_mmx);
776 } else {
777 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_4bit_x86;
778 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_4bit_x86);
779 }
780# else
781 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_4bit;
782 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_4bit);
783# endif
784# elif defined(GHASH_ASM_ARM)
785# ifdef PMULL_CAPABLE
786 if (PMULL_CAPABLE) {
787 gcm_init_v8(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
788 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_v8;
789 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_v8);
790 } else
791# endif
792# ifdef NEON_CAPABLE
793 if (NEON_CAPABLE) {
794 gcm_init_neon(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
795 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_neon;
796 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_neon);
797 } else
798# endif
799 {
800 gcm_init_4bit(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
801 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_4bit;
802 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_4bit);
803 }
804# elif defined(GHASH_ASM_SPARC)
805 if (OPENSSL_sparcv9cap_P[0] & SPARCV9_VIS3) {
806 gcm_init_vis3(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
807 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_vis3;
808 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_vis3);
809 } else {
810 gcm_init_4bit(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
811 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_4bit;
812 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_4bit);
813 }
814# elif defined(GHASH_ASM_PPC)
815 if (OPENSSL_ppccap_P & PPC_CRYPTO207) {
816 gcm_init_p8(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
817 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_p8;
818 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_p8);
819 } else {
820 gcm_init_4bit(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
821 ctx->gmult = gcm_gmult_4bit;
822 CTX__GHASH(gcm_ghash_4bit);
823 }
824# else
825 gcm_init_4bit(ctx->Htable, ctx->H.u);
826# endif
827# undef CTX__GHASH
828#endif
829}

831void CRYPTO_gcm128_setiv(GCM128_CONTEXT *ctx, const unsigned char *iv,
832 size_t len)
833{
834 const union {
835 long one;
836 char little;
837 } is_endian = { 1 };
838 unsigned int ctr;
839#ifdef GCM_FUNCREF_4BIT
840 void (*gcm_gmult_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16]) = ctx->gmult;
841#endif
842
843 ctx->len.u[0] = 0; /* AAD length */
844 ctx->len.u[1] = 0; /* message length */
845 ctx->ares = 0;
846 ctx->mres = 0;
847
848 if (len == 12) {
849 memcpy(ctx->Yi.c, iv, 12);
850 ctx->Yi.c[12] = 0;
851 ctx->Yi.c[13] = 0;
852 ctx->Yi.c[14] = 0;
853 ctx->Yi.c[15] = 1;
854 ctr = 1;
855 } else {
856 size_t i;
857 u64 len0 = len;
858
859 /* Borrow ctx->Xi to calculate initial Yi */
860 ctx->Xi.u[0] = 0;
861 ctx->Xi.u[1] = 0;
862
863 while (len >= 16) {
864 for (i = 0; i < 16; ++i)
865 ctx->Xi.c[i] ^= iv[i];
866 GCM_MUL(ctx);
867 iv += 16;
868 len -= 16;
869 }
870 if (len) {
871 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
872 ctx->Xi.c[i] ^= iv[i];
873 GCM_MUL(ctx);
874 }
875 len0 <<= 3;
876 if (is_endian.little) {
877#ifdef BSWAP8
878 ctx->Xi.u[1] ^= BSWAP8(len0);
879#else
880 ctx->Xi.c[8] ^= (u8)(len0 >> 56);
881 ctx->Xi.c[9] ^= (u8)(len0 >> 48);
882 ctx->Xi.c[10] ^= (u8)(len0 >> 40);
883 ctx->Xi.c[11] ^= (u8)(len0 >> 32);
884 ctx->Xi.c[12] ^= (u8)(len0 >> 24);
885 ctx->Xi.c[13] ^= (u8)(len0 >> 16);
886 ctx->Xi.c[14] ^= (u8)(len0 >> 8);
887 ctx->Xi.c[15] ^= (u8)(len0);
888#endif
889 } else {
890 ctx->Xi.u[1] ^= len0;
891 }
892
893 GCM_MUL(ctx);
894
895 if (is_endian.little)
896#ifdef BSWAP4
897 ctr = BSWAP4(ctx->Xi.d[3]);
898#else
899 ctr = GETU32(ctx->Xi.c + 12);
900#endif
901 else
902 ctr = ctx->Xi.d[3];
903
904 /* Copy borrowed Xi to Yi */
905 ctx->Yi.u[0] = ctx->Xi.u[0];
906 ctx->Yi.u[1] = ctx->Xi.u[1];
907 }
908
909 ctx->Xi.u[0] = 0;
910 ctx->Xi.u[1] = 0;
911
912 (*ctx->block) (ctx->Yi.c, ctx->EK0.c, ctx->key);
913 ++ctr;
914 if (is_endian.little)
915#ifdef BSWAP4
916 ctx->Yi.d[3] = BSWAP4(ctr);
917#else
918 PUTU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12, ctr);
919#endif
920 else
921 ctx->Yi.d[3] = ctr;
922}

924int CRYPTO_gcm128_aad(GCM128_CONTEXT *ctx, const unsigned char *aad,
925 size_t len)
926{
927 size_t i;
928 unsigned int n;
929 u64 alen = ctx->len.u[0];
930#ifdef GCM_FUNCREF_4BIT
931 void (*gcm_gmult_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16]) = ctx->gmult;
932# ifdef GHASH
933 void (*gcm_ghash_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16],
934 const u8 *inp, size_t len) = ctx->ghash;
935# endif
936#endif
937
938 if (ctx->len.u[1])
939 return -2;
940
941 alen += len;
942 if (alen > (U64(1) << 61) || (sizeof(len) == 8 && alen < len))
943 return -1;
944 ctx->len.u[0] = alen;
945
946 n = ctx->ares;
947 if (n) {
948 while (n && len) {
949 ctx->Xi.c[n] ^= *(aad++);
950 --len;
951 n = (n + 1) % 16;
952 }
953 if (n == 0)
954 GCM_MUL(ctx);
955 else {
956 ctx->ares = n;
957 return 0;
958 }
959 }
960#ifdef GHASH
961 if ((i = (len & (size_t)-16))) {
962 GHASH(ctx, aad, i);
963 aad += i;
964 len -= i;
965 }
966#else
967 while (len >= 16) {
968 for (i = 0; i < 16; ++i)
969 ctx->Xi.c[i] ^= aad[i];
970 GCM_MUL(ctx);
971 aad += 16;
972 len -= 16;
973 }
974#endif
975 if (len) {
976 n = (unsigned int)len;
977 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i)
978 ctx->Xi.c[i] ^= aad[i];
979 }
980
981 ctx->ares = n;
982 return 0;
983}

985int CRYPTO_gcm128_encrypt(GCM128_CONTEXT *ctx,
986 const unsigned char *in, unsigned char *out,
987 size_t len)
988{
989 const union {
990 long one;
991 char little;
992 } is_endian = { 1 };
993 unsigned int n, ctr, mres;
994 size_t i;
995 u64 mlen = ctx->len.u[1];
996 block128_f block = ctx->block;
997 void *key = ctx->key;
998#ifdef GCM_FUNCREF_4BIT
999 void (*gcm_gmult_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16]) = ctx->gmult;
1000# if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1001 void (*gcm_ghash_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16],
1002 const u8 *inp, size_t len) = ctx->ghash;
1003# endif
1004#endif
1005
1006 mlen += len;
1007 if (mlen > ((U64(1) << 36) - 32) || (sizeof(len) == 8 && mlen < len))
1008 return -1;
1009 ctx->len.u[1] = mlen;
1010
1011 mres = ctx->mres;
1012
1013 if (ctx->ares) {
1014 /* First call to encrypt finalizes GHASH(AAD) */
1015#if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1016 if (len == 0) {
1017 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1018 ctx->ares = 0;
1019 return 0;
1020 }
1021 memcpy(ctx->Xn, ctx->Xi.c, sizeof(ctx->Xi));
1022 ctx->Xi.u[0] = 0;
1023 ctx->Xi.u[1] = 0;
1024 mres = sizeof(ctx->Xi);
1025#else
1026 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1027#endif
1028 ctx->ares = 0;
1029 }
1030
1031 if (is_endian.little)
1032#ifdef BSWAP4
1033 ctr = BSWAP4(ctx->Yi.d[3]);
1034#else
1035 ctr = GETU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12);
1036#endif
1037 else
1038 ctr = ctx->Yi.d[3];
1039
1040 n = mres % 16;
1041#if !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1042 if (16 % sizeof(size_t) == 0) { /* always true actually */
1043 do {
1044 if (n) {
1045# if defined(GHASH)
1046 while (n && len) {
1047 ctx->Xn[mres++] = *(out++) = *(in++) ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1048 --len;
1049 n = (n + 1) % 16;
1050 }
1051 if (n == 0) {
1052 GHASH(ctx, ctx->Xn, mres);
1053 mres = 0;
1054 } else {
1055 ctx->mres = mres;

1220int CRYPTO_gcm128_decrypt(GCM128_CONTEXT *ctx,
1221 const unsigned char *in, unsigned char *out,
1222 size_t len)
1223{
1224 const union {
1225 long one;
1226 char little;
1227 } is_endian = { 1 };
1228 unsigned int n, ctr, mres;
1229 size_t i;
1230 u64 mlen = ctx->len.u[1];
1231 block128_f block = ctx->block;
1232 void *key = ctx->key;
1233#ifdef GCM_FUNCREF_4BIT
1234 void (*gcm_gmult_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16]) = ctx->gmult;
1235# if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1236 void (*gcm_ghash_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16],
1237 const u8 *inp, size_t len) = ctx->ghash;
1238# endif
1239#endif

1241 mlen += len;
1242 if (mlen > ((U64(1) << 36) - 32) || (sizeof(len) == 8 && mlen < len))
1243 return -1;
1244 ctx->len.u[1] = mlen;
1245
1246 mres = ctx->mres;
1247
1248 if (ctx->ares) {
1249 /* First call to decrypt finalizes GHASH(AAD) */
1250#if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1251 if (len == 0) {
1252 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1253 ctx->ares = 0;
1254 return 0;
1255 }

1257 ctx->Xi.u[0] = 0;
1258 ctx->Xi.u[1] = 0;
1259 mres = sizeof(ctx->Xi);
1260#else
1261 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1262#endif
1263 ctx->ares = 0;
1264 }
1265
1266 if (is_endian.little)
1267#ifdef BSWAP4
1268 ctr = BSWAP4(ctx->Yi.d[3]);
1269#else
1270 ctr = GETU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12);
1271#endif
1272 else
1273 ctr = ctx->Yi.d[3];
1274
1275 n = mres % 16;
1276#if !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1277 if (16 % sizeof(size_t) == 0) { /* always true actually */
1278 do {
1279 if (n) {
1280# if defined(GHASH)
1281 while (n && len) {
1282 *(out++) = (ctx->Xn[mres++] = *(in++)) ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1283 --len;
1284 n = (n + 1) % 16;
1285 }
1286 if (n == 0) {
1287 GHASH(ctx, ctx->Xn, mres);
1288 mres = 0;
1289 } else {
1290 ctx->mres = mres;
1291 return 0;
1292 }
1293# else
1294 while (n && len) {
1295 u8 c = *(in++);
1296 *(out++) = c ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1297 ctx->Xi.c[n] ^= c;
1298 --len;
1299 n = (n + 1) % 16;
1300 }
1301 if (n == 0) {
1302 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1303 mres = 0;
1304 } else {
1305 ctx->mres = n;
1306 return 0;
1307 }
1308# endif
1309 }
1310# if defined(STRICT_ALIGNMENT)
1311 if (((size_t)in | (size_t)out) % sizeof(size_t) != 0)
1312 break;
1313# endif
1314# if defined(GHASH)
1315 if (len >= 16 && mres) {
1316 GHASH(ctx, ctx->Xn, mres);
1317 mres = 0;
1318 }
1319# if defined(GHASH_CHUNK)
1320 while (len >= GHASH_CHUNK) {
1321 size_t j = GHASH_CHUNK;

1324 while (j) {

1326 const size_t *in_t = (const size_t *)in;
1327
1328 (*block) (ctx->Yi.c, ctx->EKi.c, key);

1330 if (is_endian.little)
1331# ifdef BSWAP4

1346# endif
1347 if ((i = (len & (size_t)-16))) {

1350 size_t *out_t = (size_t *)out;

1365 out += 16;
1366 in += 16;
1367 len -= 16;
1368 }
1369 }
1370# else
1371 while (len >= 16) {
1372 size_t *out_t = (size_t *)out;
1373 const size_t *in_t = (const size_t *)in;
1374
1375 (*block) (ctx->Yi.c, ctx->EKi.c, key);
1376 ++ctr;
1377 if (is_endian.little)
1378# ifdef BSWAP4
1379 ctx->Yi.d[3] = BSWAP4(ctr);
1380# else
1381 PUTU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12, ctr);
1382# endif
1383 else
1384 ctx->Yi.d[3] = ctr;
1385 for (i = 0; i < 16 / sizeof(size_t); ++i) {

1388 ctx->Xi.t[i] ^= c;
1389 }
1390 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1391 out += 16;
1392 in += 16;
1393 len -= 16;
1394 }
1395# endif
1396 if (len) {
1397 (*block) (ctx->Yi.c, ctx->EKi.c, key);
1398 ++ctr;
1399 if (is_endian.little)
1400# ifdef BSWAP4
1401 ctx->Yi.d[3] = BSWAP4(ctr);
1402# else
1403 PUTU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12, ctr);
1404# endif
1405 else
1406 ctx->Yi.d[3] = ctr;
1407# if defined(GHASH)
1408 while (len--) {
1409 out[n] = (ctx->Xn[mres++] = in[n]) ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1410 ++n;
1411 }
1412# else
1413 while (len--) {
1414 u8 c = in[n];
1415 ctx->Xi.c[n] ^= c;
1416 out[n] = c ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1417 ++n;
1418 }
1419 mres = n;
1420# endif
1421 }
1422
1423 ctx->mres = mres;
1424 return 0;
1425 } while (0);
1426 }
1427#endif
1428 for (i = 0; i < len; ++i) {
1429 u8 c;
1430 if (n == 0) {
1431 (*block) (ctx->Yi.c, ctx->EKi.c, key);
1432 ++ctr;
1433 if (is_endian.little)
1434#ifdef BSWAP4
1435 ctx->Yi.d[3] = BSWAP4(ctr);
1436#else
1437 PUTU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12, ctr);
1438#endif
1439 else
1440 ctx->Yi.d[3] = ctr;
1441 }
1442#if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1443 out[i] = (ctx->Xn[mres++] = c = in[i]) ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1444 n = (n + 1) % 16;
1445 if (mres == sizeof(ctx->Xn)) {
1446 GHASH(ctx,ctx->Xn,sizeof(ctx->Xn));
1447 mres = 0;
1448 }
1449#else
1450 c = in[i];
1451 out[i] = c ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1452 ctx->Xi.c[n] ^= c;
1453 mres = n = (n + 1) % 16;
1454 if (n == 0)
1455 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1456#endif
1457 }
1458
1459 ctx->mres = mres;
1460 return 0;
1461}

1732 else
1733 ctx->Yi.d[3] = ctr;
1734 out += GHASH_CHUNK;
1735 in += GHASH_CHUNK;
1736 len -= GHASH_CHUNK;
1737 }
1738# endif
1739# endif
1740 if ((i = (len & (size_t)-16))) {
1741 size_t j = i / 16;
1742
1743# if defined(GHASH)
1744 GHASH(ctx, in, i);
1745# else
1746 while (j--) {
1747 size_t k;
1748 for (k = 0; k < 16; ++k)
1749 ctx->Xi.c[k] ^= in[k];
1750 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1751 in += 16;
1752 }
1753 j = i / 16;
1754 in -= i;
1755# endif
1756 (*stream) (in, out, j, key, ctx->Yi.c);
1757 ctr += (unsigned int)j;
1758 if (is_endian.little)
1759# ifdef BSWAP4
1760 ctx->Yi.d[3] = BSWAP4(ctr);
1761# else
1762 PUTU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12, ctr);
1763# endif
1764 else
1765 ctx->Yi.d[3] = ctr;
1766 out += i;
1767 in += i;
1768 len -= i;
1769 }
1770 if (len) {
1771 (*ctx->block) (ctx->Yi.c, ctx->EKi.c, key);
1772 ++ctr;
1773 if (is_endian.little)
1774# ifdef BSWAP4
1775 ctx->Yi.d[3] = BSWAP4(ctr);
1776# else
1777 PUTU32(ctx->Yi.c + 12, ctr);
1778# endif
1779 else
1780 ctx->Yi.d[3] = ctr;
1781 while (len--) {
1782# if defined(GHASH)
1783 out[n] = (ctx->Xn[mres++] = in[n]) ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1784# else
1785 u8 c = in[n];
1786 ctx->Xi.c[mres++] ^= c;
1787 out[n] = c ^ ctx->EKi.c[n];
1788# endif
1789 ++n;
1790 }
1791 }
1792
1793 ctx->mres = mres;
1794 return 0;
1795#endif
1796}
1797
1798int CRYPTO_gcm128_finish(GCM128_CONTEXT *ctx, const unsigned char *tag,
1799 size_t len)
1800{
1801 const union {
1802 long one;
1803 char little;
1804 } is_endian = { 1 };
1805 u64 alen = ctx->len.u[0] << 3;
1806 u64 clen = ctx->len.u[1] << 3;
1807#ifdef GCM_FUNCREF_4BIT
1808 void (*gcm_gmult_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16]) = ctx->gmult;
1809# if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1810 void (*gcm_ghash_p) (u64 Xi[2], const u128 Htable[16],
1811 const u8 *inp, size_t len) = ctx->ghash;
1812# endif
1813#endif
1814
1815#if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1816 u128 bitlen;
1817 unsigned int mres = ctx->mres;
1818
1819 if (mres) {
1820 unsigned blocks = (mres + 15) & -16;
1821
1822 memset(ctx->Xn + mres, 0, blocks - mres);
1823 mres = blocks;
1824 if (mres == sizeof(ctx->Xn)) {
1825 GHASH(ctx, ctx->Xn, mres);
1826 mres = 0;
1827 }
1828 } else if (ctx->ares) {
1829 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1830 }
1831#else
1832 if (ctx->mres || ctx->ares)
1833 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1834#endif
1835
1836 if (is_endian.little) {
1837#ifdef BSWAP8
1838 alen = BSWAP8(alen);
1839 clen = BSWAP8(clen);
1840#else
1841 u8 *p = ctx->len.c;
1842
1843 ctx->len.u[0] = alen;
1844 ctx->len.u[1] = clen;
1845
1846 alen = (u64)GETU32(p) << 32 | GETU32(p + 4);
1847 clen = (u64)GETU32(p + 8) << 32 | GETU32(p + 12);
1848#endif
1849 }
1850
1851#if defined(GHASH) && !defined(OPENSSL_SMALL_FOOTPRINT)
1852 bitlen.hi = alen;
1853 bitlen.lo = clen;
1854 memcpy(ctx->Xn + mres, &bitlen, sizeof(bitlen));
1855 mres += sizeof(bitlen);
1856 GHASH(ctx, ctx->Xn, mres);
1857#else
1858 ctx->Xi.u[0] ^= alen;
1859 ctx->Xi.u[1] ^= clen;
1860 GCM_MUL(ctx);
1861#endif
1862
1863 ctx->Xi.u[0] ^= ctx->EK0.u[0];
1864 ctx->Xi.u[1] ^= ctx->EK0.u[1];
1865
1866 if (tag && len <= sizeof(ctx->Xi))
1867 return CRYPTO_memcmp(ctx->Xi.c, tag, len);
1868 else
1869 return -1;
1870}
1871
1872void CRYPTO_gcm128_tag(GCM128_CONTEXT *ctx, unsigned char *tag, size_t len)
1873{
1874 CRYPTO_gcm128_finish(ctx, NULL, 0);
1875 memcpy(tag, ctx->Xi.c,
1876 len <= sizeof(ctx->Xi.c) ? len : sizeof(ctx->Xi.c));
1877}
